The 11Be beam was produced by the ISOL method using
primary 500 MeV proton beam. The beam purity of 11Be
was enhanced using the TRIUMF Laser Ionization Source
TRILIS. A mass-separated beam of 11Be was delivered
to the experiment with an intensity of 10E+5 pps.

x4codes.hlp: Hyperpure Germanium detector

x4freetext: For gamma ray detection an array of twelve
high-purity germanium clovers of TIGRESS at a
target-to-detector distance of 14.5 cm was used. Each
clover consists of four eightfold segmented crystals
in a common cryostat, surrounded by a bismuth
germanate Compton-suppression shield. Eight clovers
were positioned at theta(LAB) =90 deg and four at
theta(LAB) =135 deg.

x4codes.hlp: Coincidence

x4freetext: Coincidence between charged particle telescope
and 320 kev Gamma ray in HPGe array was required.
Gamma ray energy was corrected for Doppler shift
